Former President of the Senate, Senator David Mark, has described former Nigerian President, Olusegun Obasanjo as an uncommon leader, who believes in the sanctity of a united Nigeria and Africa at large. Senator David Mark, who also served as a military governor of Niger State, and communication Minister, sees Obasanjo as a patriotic African leader who is passionate about the peace, unity and development of the continent. Mark, while congratulating him on his 85th birthday, noted that, Obasanjo’s
frontline role in the battle that ended the 30 months old Nigeria/Biafra fratricidal war remains a reference point in the history and evolution of Nigeria He praised the celebrant for his untiring efforts in ensuring peace in Nigeria and Africa pointing out that “his indomitable spirit is inspiring and reassuring.“ He urged new generation of leaders to emulate the virtues of Obasanjo because “his kind is what we need to make the nation peaceful, united and to uphold our bond of brotherhood.” According to him, Former president Obasanjo, both as a Military Head-of-State and as civilian president, has left no one in doubt of his political will to uphold the sanctity of our unity as one indivisible Nigeria. The former Senate President enjoined Obasanjo to continue to make his reservoir of knowledge and wealth of experience available to the younger generation to tap from. He prayed that God in His infinite mercies continues to grant Obasanjo good health, wisdom and courage in the years ahead.